                    "verdict": "malicious",
                    "source": "palm",
                    "category": "code_insight",
                    "analysis": "This is a sample of the Nefilim ransomware, as indicated by the PDB path `...\\Release\\NEFILIM.pdb` and multiple behavioral indicators. The malware enumerates files on logical drives, skipping critical system directories and specific file extensions to avoid damaging the OS. It encrypts files using a combination of RSA and RC4 (`CryptImportKey`, `CryptDeriveKey`, `CryptEncrypt`) and appends the `.NEFILIM` extension to encrypted files. It drops a ransom note named `NEFILIM-DECRYPT.txt` by decrypting an embedded blob. To ensure only one instance runs, it creates a mutex with the name `Den'gi plyvut v karmany rekoy. My khodim po krayu nozha...`. Finally, it attempts to delete its own executable using a command like `cmd.exe /c timeout /t 3 /nobreak && del ...`.",
                    "id": "5ab834f599c6ad35fcd0a168d93c52c399c6de7d1c20f33e25cb1fdb25aec9c6-file-palm"
